# Build Luxury Chauffeur Website

We will build a completely new multi-page website from scratch, utilizing standard HTML5, CSS3, and modern JavaScript, with a strong emphasis on a premium, luxury aesthetic. The website will be located at a new directory `c:\Users\ashle\OneDrive\Documents\Antigravity\dap-executive\`.

## User Review Required

- Is `c:\Users\ashle\OneDrive\Documents\Antigravity\dap-executive\` the correct directory to create this project? 
- We will be using raw HTML, CSS, and JS (no build tools like Webpack or frameworks like React/Next.js) to keep things lightweight yet highly performant and easy to deploy anywhere. Does this approach work for you?

## Proposed Changes

We will create the following files to satisfy the multi-page structure and luxury design requirements:

### Core Layout & Styles
#### [NEW] [main.css](file:///c:/Users/ashle/OneDrive/Documents/Antigravity/dap-executive/css/main.css)
Will contain the luxury design system:
- Midnight Navy, Platinum, Charcoal color palette.
- Modern typography variables (Playfair Display for headings, Inter for body).
- Reusable UI component styles (Glassmorphism containers, premium buttons, input fields).
- Layout grids and flexbox classes.
- Smooth scroll animations, hover states, and responsive queries.

#### [NEW] [main.js](file:///c:/Users/ashle/OneDrive/Documents/Antigravity/dap-executive/js/main.js)
Will contain core interactivity:
- Mobile navigation toggle.
- Scroll observer for initializing reveal animations.
- Form interactions (basic validation visually).

### Pages
